{"title_page": "Joe Pera", "text_new": "{{short description|American comedian}}\n{{Use American English|date = December 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Joe Pera\n| image         = Joe Pera (6176423956).jpg\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = Pera in September 2011\n| birth_name    = Joseph Pera\n| birth_place   = [[Buffalo, New York|Buffalo]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.\n| alma_mater    = [[Ithaca College]]\n| yearsactive   = 2009\u2013present\n| module             = {{Infobox comedian|embed=yes\n| medium       = {{flatlist|\n* Stand-up\n* television\n* film\n}}\n| genre        = {{flatlist|\n* [[Observational comedy]]\n* [[character comedy]]\n* [[sketch comedy]]\n}}\n| subject      = {{flatlist|\n* [[American culture]]\n* [[everyday life]]\n* [[popular culture|pop culture]]\n* [[embarrassment|social awkwardness]]}}\n}}\n}}\n'''Joseph Pera'''<ref name=\"Pera1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/pop-culture/2014/02/comedians-under-30-to-check-out-this-year/joe-pera|title=Comedians Under 30 To Check Out This Year|website=Complex|last=Burke|first=Jason|date=February 18, 2014|accessdate=May 11, 2018}}</ref> is an American comedian, writer and actor. He is best known as the creator and star of [[Adult Swim]]'s ''[[Joe Pera Talks with You]]''.\n\n==Early life==\nJoe Pera was born in [[New York, New York]], where he claims to be \"familiar with the trees up there.\" He studied film at [[Ithaca College]], where he competed and won the college's stand-up competition three times.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://massmoca.org/joe-pera/|title=Joe Pera|date=2016-06-01|work=MASS MoCA|access-date=2018-07-27|language=en-US}}</ref> After that, he moved to New York City to pursue comedy and would attend open microphone nights as often as possible.<ref name=\"Pera2\">{{cite web|url=http://texastravesty.com/interview/04/25/2018/interview-joe-pera|title=Interview with Joe Pera|date=April 25, 2018|website=Texas Travesty|accessdate=May 11, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180512113141/http://texastravesty.com/interview/04/25/2018/interview-joe-pera|archive-date=May 12, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nKnown for his slow, \"grandfatherly\" delivery and his penchant for wearing sweaters, Pera created the [[Adult Swim]] [[Infomercials (TV specials)|Infomercial]] ''Joe Pera Talks You to Sleep''. This was followed by an appearance on ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]'', and another stand-alone Adult Swim special titled ''Joe Pera Helps You Find the Perfect Christmas Tree''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://buffalonews.com/2016/12/09/let-joe-pera-help-find-christmas-tree/|title=Let Joe Pera help you find a Christmas tree|website=Buffalo News|last=Ciemcioch|first=Mark|date=December 9, 2016|accessdate=May 11, 2018}}</ref> Thanks to the success of those programs (all produced by Chestnut Walnut, founded by him and [[Conner O'Malley]]),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.brooklynfilmfestival.org/films/detail.asp?fid=1677 |title=Peaceful Reflections Of The Apocalypse by Tom Hunt \u2013 Animation Film @ Brooklyn Film Festival |publisher=Brooklynfilmfestival.org |date=2018-04-27 |accessdate=2018-08-01}}</ref> Pera developed a television series for Adult Swim, which premiered on May 20, 2018, titled ''[[Joe Pera Talks with You]]''.<ref name=\"Pera2\" /> He appeared on  ''[[Conan (talk show)]]'' on March 28, 2017, ''[[The Late Show with Stephen Colbert]]'' on Dec. 4, 2019.\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year!!Title!!Role!!Notes\n|-\n|2017\n| ''Snowy Bing Bongs Across the North Star Combat Zone''\n| Jim\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year!!Title!!Role!!Notes\n|-\n|2013\u201314\n| ''[[The Chris Gethard Show]]''\n| Zero Fucks Boyd\n| 4 episodes\n|-\n| 2014\n|''New Timers''     \n| Myron\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2016\n| ''Joe Pera Talks You to Sleep''\n| Himself\n| Short; part of ''[[Infomercials (TV specials)|Infomercials]]''\n|-\n| ''Joe Pera Helps You Find the Perfect Christmas Tree''\n| Himself\n|\n|-\n| 2017\n|''[[Conan (talk show)|Conan]]''     \n| Himself\n| 3/28/17\n|-\n| 2019\n|''[[The Late Show with Stephen Colbert]]''     \n| Himself\n| 12/4/19\n|-\n| 2019\n|''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]''     \n| Himself\n| 12/18/19\n|-\n| 2018\u2013present\n| ''[[Joe Pera Talks with You]]''\n| Himself\n| 20 episodes; also creator, executive producer and writer\n|}\n\n===YouTube Series===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year!!Title!!Role!!Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2014\n| Perfect Week\n| Himself\n| 7 episode mini-series hosted by JASH with trailer\n|-\n| The Pancake Breakfast Critic\n| Himself\n| 3 episode mini-series hosted by MTV\n|-\n|2015\n|How To Make It In USA\n|Himself\n|9 episode mini-series co-starring [[Conner O'Malley]]\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official}}\n* {{IMDb name}}\n*''[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=trfHP5LHVNY Joe Pera Talks You to Sleep]'' on [[YouTube]]\n* [http://www.chestnutwalnutunlimited.com/ Chestnut Walnut Unlimited website]\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pera, Joe}}\n[[Category:21st-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male writers]]\n[[Category:American comedy writers]]\n[[Category:American male comedians]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:American stand-up comedians]]\n[[Category:American television writers]]\n[[Category:Comedians from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Ithaca College alumni]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Buffalo, New York]]\n[[Category:Male television writers]]\n[[Category:Writers from Buffalo, New York]]\n[[Category:Screenwriters from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Television personalities from New York (state)]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Americ